3. cs.MM (Multimedia) is another possible category as the paper deals with image processing and analysis. 
4. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also possible as the paper discusses the ability of the proposed model to predict human fixation data. 
5. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper proposes a new bottom-up paradigm for detecting visual saliency.
